@@ -0,0 +1,83 @@
+# PictureInPicture
+
+## Class: PictureInPicture
+
+> A handle for the currently active Picture-in-Picture window.
+
+Process: [Main](../glossary.md#main-process)<br />
+_This class is not exported from the `'electron'` module. It is only available as a return value of other methods in the Electron API._
+
+`PictureInPicture` instances are tied to the PiP session that created them. If
+the PiP window is closed and another PiP window is opened later, methods on the
+old handle will not affect the new PiP window.
+
+### Instance Methods
+
+#### `pip.getBounds()`
+
+Returns `Rectangle | null` - The current PiP window
+bounds in screen coordinates, or `null` if this handle is no longer active.
+
+#### `pip.setBounds(bounds)`
+
+* `bounds` [Rectangle](structures/rectangle.md)
+
+Returns `Rectangle | null` - The actual PiP window
+bounds after Chromium and the operating system apply minimum size, maximum
+size, work area, and aspect-ratio constraints. Returns `null` if this handle is
+no longer active.
+
+#### `pip.getSize()`
+
+Returns `Size | null` - The current PiP window size, or
+`null` if this handle is no longer active.
+
+#### `pip.setSize(size)`
+
+* `size` [Size](structures/size.md)
+
+Returns `Size | null` - The actual PiP window size after
+constraints are applied. The current PiP window origin is preserved. Returns
+`null` if this handle is no longer active.
+
+#### `pip.getSourceId()`
+
+Returns `string | null` - The `chromeMediaSourceId` for this PiP window, or
+`null` if one is not available on the current platform or this handle is no
+longer active.
+
+#### `pip.getSource([options])`
+
+* `options` [PictureInPictureSourceOptions](structures/picture-in-picture-source-options.md) (optional)
+
+Returns `Promise<DesktopCapturerSource | null>` - fulfilled with this PiP window
+as a [`DesktopCapturerSource`](structures/desktop-capturer-source.md), or `null`
+if one is not available on the current platform or this handle is no longer
+active.
+
+When the platform desktop source enumerator does not list the PiP window
+directly, Electron may return a source with an empty thumbnail and app icon. Its
+`id` is still usable as a `chromeMediaSourceId` constraint.
+
+#### `pip.close()`
+
+Returns `boolean` - Whether this PiP window was closed.
+
+#### `pip.isDestroyed()`
+
+Returns `boolean` - Whether this handle no longer points to the active PiP
+session.
+
+### Instance Properties
+
+#### `pip.id` _Readonly_
+
+A `number` that identifies the PiP session.
+
+#### `pip.type` _Readonly_
+
+A `string` identifying the PiP kind. Can be `video` or `document`.
+
+#### `pip.sourceWebContents` _Readonly_
+
+A [`WebContents`](web-contents.md) that opened or owns this PiP window.
