+# VideoPictureInPicture
+
+## Class: VideoPictureInPicture extends `PictureInPicture`
+
+> A handle for a video Picture-in-Picture window.
+
+Process: [Main](../glossary.md#main-process)<br />
+_This class is not exported from the `'electron'` module. It is only available as a return value of other methods in the Electron API._
+
+### Instance Properties
+
+#### `pip.type` _Readonly_
+
+A `string` that can be `video`.
+
+#### `pip.videoSize` _Readonly_
+
+A [`Size`](structures/size.md) representing the intrinsic size of the video
+frames shown in Picture-in-Picture.
+
+This is the video frame size, not the current PiP window size. Use
+[`pip.getSize()`](picture-in-picture.md#pipgetsize) to read the current PiP
+window size.
